caption: I really enjoyed my stay, there are ducks, lakes and many benches, also water fountains to refill your bottle, I would appreciate if fhere were some tables to study or eat lunch, otherwise it would be perfect.

Lovely park. Specially if you're visiting with children. Lots of activities for children from 6 months to 12 years. And there is even a football court for teenagers. A Well maintained, spacious  park. Totally loved the greenery.

Kellermann is a nice park, during Spring season it remains very colorful. It is a spot of lots of activities. One can also visit for workouts, to go sit and calm. I will recommend definitely visit this park.
Nice Park, on the smaller side and with a mediocre artificial pond. Nevertheless, well kept, full of trees, shade picnic friendly, lots of things for kids to do and yet not overly full of people.
A nice park to pick up food and have lunch.  Lots of shade.  It also has an impressive water feature (water fall).   Small, but well taken care of.
Beautiful park with many places to sit and a workout area. We saw a stunning sunset and it wasn't too crowded, super nice!
